        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Assad abscond</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-9-1.jpg" alt="Assad abscond" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Syria’s President Bashar al-Assad has reportedly <a href="https://www.msn.com/en-in/news/world/has-bashar-al-assad-resigned-and-fled-syria-here-s-what-russia-claims/ar-AA1vubjF?ocid=BingNewsSerp" target="_blank">left the country</a> and ordered a peaceful transition of power, according to Russia’s Foreign Ministry. Opposition groups have gained control of additional towns, with widespread celebrations marking the end of his family’s <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/08/middleeast/bashar-al-assad-syria-profile-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">50+ years</a> of rule. Freed prisoners reunited with their families, igniting hopes for dignity and democracy after nearly 14 years of <a href="https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/syria-war-timeline-assads-fall-followed-years-of-bloodshed-and-division/article68961420.ece" target="_blank">conflict</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Assad has appeared in Moscow and is being <a href="https://tass.ru/mezhdunarodnaya-panorama/22612655" target="_blank">granted</a> political asylum in Russia. 
          International responses urge stability, with <a href="https://www.aa.com.tr/en/europe/spain-voices-support-for-peaceful-stable-syria-after-assads-fall/3418233" target="_blank">Spain</a> and <a href="https://www.diplomatie.gouv.fr/fr/dossiers-pays/syrie/evenements/actualites-2024/article/syrie-chute-du-regime-de-bachar-al-assad-08-12-2024" target="_blank">France</a> advocating peaceful solutions. Meanwhile, Russia maintains heightened security at its bases in Syria, ensuring no immediate threats to its forces. Syrian rebel leaders have reportedly assured the security of Russian military bases and diplomatic sites in Syria as opposition forces gain <a href="https://meduza.io/en/news/2024/12/08/syrian-rebels-reportedly-capture-jableh-city-near-russia-s-khmeimim-airbase#:~:text=Syrian%20rebels%20have%20seized%20control%20of%20Jableh%2C%20a,the%20air%2C%20though%20the%20situation%20is%20now%20%E2%80%9Ccalm.%E2%80%9D" target="_blank">control</a> of Jableh near Russia’s Hmeymim airbase. In contrast, the Syrian Embassy’s flag and signage were removed in Moscow, according to Russian state media.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
