          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇷🇴 Romania:</strong>    
          Romanian police <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20241207-romania-police-raid-houses-linked-to-vote-probe-prosecutors" target="_blank">conducted</a> raids in Brasov on Saturday, investigating alleged irregularities in the presidential election after the constitutional court annulled the results, citing massive Russian interference. Far-right candidate Calin Georgescu’s first-round victory sparked concerns due to allegations of illegal campaign financing, social media manipulation, and over 85,000 cyberattacks linked to promoting his campaign. Georgescu <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/07/georgescu-slams-romanias-top-court-after-annulment-of-presidential-first-round" target="_blank">condemned</a> the decision as a “coup,” while President Klaus Iohannis pledged stability until a new election is organized.</p>
        </mj-text>
