          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇹🇩 Chad:</strong>   
          Hundreds <a href="https://apnews.com/article/chad-protest-france-military-agreement-0436a6c9a914c0dd007d603e279e44c8" target="_blank">protested</a> in Chad on Friday, calling for the withdrawal of French troops following the country’s decision to end a <a href="https://apnews.com/article/chad-france-defense-agreement-4f1fccb3e51199ba6f44f7a68059487a" target="_blank">defense cooperation agreement</a> with France. The protesters, chanting slogans like “Chad for us, France out!” gathered near French military bases and the French embassy. Chad’s government announced the move to redefine its strategic partnerships, though it emphasized that historical ties with France remain intact. The country has recently joined others in the region, such as Niger and Mali, in distancing itself from France as tensions over foreign military presence rise.</p>
